\DOC UNDISCH_THEN

\TYPE {UNDISCH_THEN : term -> thm_tactic -> tactic}

\SYNOPSIS
Discharges the assumption given and passes it to a theorem-tactic.

\KEYWORDS
theorem-tactic, discharge.

\DESCRIBE
{UNDISCH_THEN} finds the first assumption equal to the term given,
removes it from the assumption list, {ASSUME}s it, passes it to
the theorem-tactic and then applies the consequent tactic.  Thus:
{
   UNDISCH_THEN t f ([a1,... ai, t, aj, ... an], goal) =
     f (ASSUME t) ([a1,... ai, aj,... an], goal)
}
\noindent For example, if
{
    A ?- t
   ========  f (ASSUME "u")
    B ?- v
}
\noindent then
{
    A u {t1} ?- t
   ==============  UNDISCH_THEN t1 f
       B ?- v
}
\FAILURE
{UNDISCH_THEN} will fail for goals where the given term is not in the
assumption list.

\SEEALSO
PAT_ASSUM, DISCH, DISCH_ALL, DISCH_TAC, DISCH_THEN, NEG_DISCH,
FILTER_DISCH_TAC, FILTER_DISCH_THEN, STRIP_TAC, UNDISCH, UNDISCH_ALL,
UNDISCH_TAC.

\ENDDOC
